# Cloudflare Pages — security headers applied to every response.
#
# CSP notes:
# - script-src/style-src keep 'unsafe-inline' because a few pages (homepage, admin,
#   changelog) ship inline <script>, and inline style="" attributes are used throughout.
#   There is no build step to add per-response nonces/hashes yet. The policy still blocks
#   external script/style, eval (no 'unsafe-eval'), framing, plugins, and any non-self
#   network connection — so a stray <script src=evil> or fetch() to another origin is denied.
# - No external origins are needed today: every fetch is same-origin (/api/*, /data/*,
#   /app/), and per-trade screenshots are data: URLs (hence img-src 'self' data:).
# - Tighten script-src to hashes/nonces (drop 'unsafe-inline') after the inline scripts
#   move to their own files — see backlog A1/A2. When Stripe checkout lands, it redirects
#   (full navigation), so no CSP change is needed; embedded Stripe would need frame-src.

/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), browsing-topics=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'
